{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/add-custom-fonts-to-shopify","result":{"pageContext":{"id":752,"date":"2021-04-20T21:08:41","date_gmt":"2021-04-20T21:08:41","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=752"},"modified":"2023-02-10T03:20:28","modified_gmt":"2023-02-10T03:20:28","slug":"add-custom-fonts-to-shopify","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/add-custom-fonts-to-shopify/","title":{"rendered":"Add custom fonts to your Shopify theme [Complete Guide]"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Most Shopify themes, by default, come with a variety of Google Fonts built-in. Depending on your theme, you can easily find and change them on the Customize page of your theme and play around with a few different styles and combinations.<br><br>However, one thing that is not quite straightforward in Shopify is: how exactly can you add your own custom fonts? Say you have downloaded a new font and you have now a few <strong>.ttf, .woff</strong>, <strong>.woff2, </strong>and/or some other file extensions. How would you go about adding them to your theme and, equally important, making them the default instead of whichever font was previously being used?<br><br>In this tutorial, I&#8217;ll be teaching you how to achieve that. Also, don&#8217;t worry &#8211; no coding knowledge is required, but for more thorough customizations of how to style each specific HTML element with your font of choice, you may need some familiarity with HTML/CSS.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-making-a-backup-copy-of-your-theme\">Making a backup copy of your theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before diving into the tutorial make sure you download the theme, so in case you face any issues you can easily revert back.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1514\" height=\"481\" class=\"wp-image-503\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png 1514w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-600x191.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-1200x381.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-768x244.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1514px) 100vw, 1514px\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-step-1-adding-the-font-files-to-your-store\">Step 1: Adding the font files to your store</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing that we have to do is to add the fonts to the Shopify store. From there, we can reference it via code and use it in our theme.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>From your Shopify admin, navigate to <strong>Settings &gt; Files</strong>.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"946\" height=\"890\" class=\"wp-image-2073\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf1.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf1.jpg 946w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf1-850x800.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf1-768x723.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 946px) 100vw, 946px\" /><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"438\" height=\"842\" class=\"wp-image-2077\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf3.jpg\" alt=\"\"><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Click on <strong>upload files</strong> at the top right and upload all of your font files. Web Font files are the ones that have the following extensions:<strong> .ttf</strong>, <strong>.woff</strong>,.<strong>woff2</strong>, <strong>.eot</strong>, <strong>.svg</strong> or <strong>.otf</strong>. <br><br>Therefore, make sure you upload all font files that came with the <strong>.zip</strong>, or at least the ones you want to use. <br><br>In this case, I have one single font file with the <strong><strong>.</strong>otf</strong> format, so I&#8217;ll be uploading only this one.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1448\" height=\"687\" class=\"wp-image-2091\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13.jpg 1448w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13-850x403.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13-1200x569.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13-768x364.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1448px) 100vw, 1448px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Once you have uploaded all of your font files, it&#8217;s time to add some code to read them. <br><br>Leave this tab open, though &#8211; we&#8217;ll be returning to it soon.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-step-2-adding-the-code-to-read-the-font\">Step 2: Adding the code to read the font</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>In your Shopify admin, navigate to&nbsp;<strong>Online Store</strong>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Themes&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Actions&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Edit Code</strong>.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1349\" height=\"614\" class=\"wp-image-626\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/edit-code.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/edit-code.jpg 1349w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/edit-code-600x273.jpg 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/edit-code-1200x546.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/edit-code-768x350.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1349px) 100vw, 1349px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Under <strong>sections</strong>, click on &#8220;Add a new section&#8221; and create a section named: <br><br><strong>ezfy-custom-fonts</strong><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1121\" height=\"540\" class=\"wp-image-2234\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot-fonts.png\" alt=\"Creating the ezfy-custom-fonts section in the Shopify code editor\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot-fonts.png 1121w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot-fonts-850x409.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot-fonts-768x370.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1121px) 100vw, 1121px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paste the following code and save:<br><br>[gist]505aacadf610fc68404ce730eee61359[gist]<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1485\" height=\"772\" class=\"wp-image-2103\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/c18.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/c18.jpg 1485w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/c18-850x442.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/c18-1200x624.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/c18-768x399.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1485px) 100vw, 1485px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Now, open the file named<strong> theme.liquid. </strong>Make sure it reads exactly &#8220;theme.liquid&#8221;.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1561\" height=\"718\" class=\"wp-image-2079\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf5.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf5.jpg 1561w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf5-850x391.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf5-1200x552.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf5-768x353.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf5-1536x707.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1561px) 100vw, 1561px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Search for:<br><br>&lt;body<br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paste the following code right <strong>below</strong> the line you found:<br><br><code>{% section 'ezfy-custom-fonts' %}</code></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"723\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/cf6-1200x723.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2087\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/cf6-1200x723.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/cf6-850x512.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/cf6-768x463.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/cf6.jpg 1393w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-step-3-using-the-custom-font-on-your-website\">Step 3: Using the custom font on your website</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>On the top left, click on the 3 dots and &#8220;customize theme&#8221;.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1319\" height=\"727\" class=\"wp-image-2081\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf10.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf10.jpg 1319w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf10-850x468.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf10-1200x661.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf10-768x423.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1319px) 100vw, 1319px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>On the sidebar located on the left side, you will find a new section called &#8220;EZFY Custom Font&#8221;.<br><br>Click on the arrow on the left to expand it, and then click on &#8220;Add font&#8221;.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"950\" height=\"616\" class=\"wp-image-2085\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf11.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf11.jpg 950w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf11-850x551.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf11-768x498.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 950px) 100vw, 950px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Under &#8220;Custom font name&#8221;, make sure you add a descriptive name. It can be anything you wish. <br><br>My font&#8217;s name is &#8220;Cloud&#8221;, so I&#8217;ll be adding that. <br><br>Now, under &#8220;Custom font URL&#8221;, add the URL for the file that was added back in step 2. Simply click on the chain icon to get the font&#8217;s URL.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1448\" height=\"687\" class=\"wp-image-2091\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13.jpg 1448w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13-850x403.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13-1200x569.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf13-768x364.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1448px) 100vw, 1448px\" /><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1069\" height=\"730\" class=\"wp-image-2093\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf16.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf16.jpg 1069w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf16-850x580.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf16-768x524.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1069px) 100vw, 1069px\" /><br></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<p>On the screenshot above you can see that the font is immediately loaded right on the Customize page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can select which HTML elements should display your custom font, as well as add as many fonts you&#8217;d like. <br><br>Bear in mind that whatever font is first in the list will always overwrite the ones below it. Therefore, if you have added 5 fonts and assigned the &#8220;H1&#8221; for all 5 of them, the &#8220;H1&#8221; will use only the very first font in the list.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-extra-adding-the-custom-font-only-to-specific-elements\">Extra: adding the custom font only to specific elements</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If you&#8217;d like to use your custom font only for specific elements, you can use the &#8220;CSS Selectors&#8221; and add your selector there. Continue reading below to learn how to find your website&#8217;s CSS selector.</p>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>While in the page containing the element whose font you wish to change, press <strong><code>CRTL + shift + c</code></strong> to open your browser&#8217;s developer tools in inspection mode. If you&#8217;re using a Mac, that&#8217;s <strong><code>CMD + shift + c</code></strong> instead.<br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Find the text you want to change the font of and click it. This will highlight the element in the HTML.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1365\" height=\"617\" class=\"wp-image-1960\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_2.png\" alt=\"Selecting an element in the Impulse theme product page\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_2.png 1365w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_2-850x384.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_2-1200x542.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_2-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1365px) 100vw, 1365px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Next, right click the element in the HTLM, go to &#8220;Copy&#8221; and click &#8220;Copy selector&#8221;. This will copy a CSS selector meant to target this exact element.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"842\" height=\"467\" class=\"wp-image-1962\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_3.png\" alt=\"Copying an element's selector from Chrome's developer's tool\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_3.png 842w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Screenshot_3-768x426.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 842px) 100vw, 842px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Now that you have your CSS selector, simply copy and paste it at the very bottom at &#8220;CSS Selectors&#8221;:<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1103\" height=\"822\" class=\"wp-image-2095\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf17.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf17.jpg 1103w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf17-850x633.jpg 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/cf17-768x572.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1103px) 100vw, 1103px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Note that this is a hard coded solution meant to select a single element, meaning that changes to your store&#8217;s HTML (specially to areas near where the font was changed) are likely to cause it to stop working. <br><br>If that happens, you can re-do this section of the tutorial or use a broader CSS selector. You can do it as many times as you want for any number of elements.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-conclusion\">Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Custom fonts are great, but use them wisely: too many fonts will end up overloading your website and taking a toll on its performance.<br><br>Remember that you can also fully disable the EZFY custom font at any time you wish by simply clicking on &#8220;EZFY Custom Font&#8221; &gt; uncheck &#8220;Enable&#8221;. <br></p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1169\" height=\"356\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-4.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2106\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-4.png 1169w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-4-850x259.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/image-4-768x234.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1169px) 100vw, 1169px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><br>You may also be interested in some other tutorials:</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/add-slideshow-shopify-no-apps\">&#8211; How to make slideshow images stop cutting off</a><br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/how-to-disable-right-click-image-and-text-copying-without-apps\">&#8211; Disable right click, image and text copying and improve your store&#8217;s security</a></p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn how to add custom fonts to your Shopify theme, step by step. Works with any web font.</p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":855,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[9],"tags":[206],"image_alt":"","featured_image_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Debut-Slider-Pro-600x338.png","featured_image_small_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Debut-Slider-Pro-200x200.png","featured_image_large_src":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Debut-Slider-Pro-1200x675.png","categories_names":["Blog"],"acf":[],"tag_names":["all themes"],"featured_image_url":"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Debut-Slider-Pro.png","featured_image_url_alt":"Add custom fonts to your Shopify theme - works with any theme","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/752"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/types/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/users/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/comments?post=752"}],"version-history":[{"count":9,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/752/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2237,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/posts/752/revisions/2237"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media/855"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/media?parent=752"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/categories?post=752"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https://www.ezfy.club/json/wp/v2/tags?post=752"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https://api.w.org/{rel}","templated":true}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["330429198","3356652627"]}